---
/**
 * FAQ section — common objections
 * Spec: What if it doesn't work? What do I need to prepare? Which channels are supported?
 */
const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What if it doesn\'t work after the session?',
    answer: 'The Done-For-You tier comes with a 100% Satisfaction Guarantee. If your agent isn\'t running perfectly after our session, you get a full refund. For Setup Call clients, I\'ll stay on the call until your agent is working.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What do I need to prepare before the session?',
    answer: 'After booking you\'ll receive a prep checklist email. The basics: make sure you have Node.js v22+ installed, your messaging platform account ready (WhatsApp, Telegram, or Discord), and any API keys you want to use (OpenAI or Anthropic). For Done-For-You clients, you\'ll also need a remote access tool like AnyDesk installed.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Which messaging channels are supported?',
    answer: 'OpenClaw supports WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, and Slack. During your session, we\'ll connect whichever channel you prefer. Additional channels can be added later.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How long does the setup actually take?',
    answer: 'A Setup Call is 60 minutes. Most clients are fully running within 45 minutes. The Done-For-You option typically takes 1-2 hours of my remote work, followed by your 30-minute handoff call.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do I need to be technical?',
    answer: 'Not at all. That\'s the whole point. Whether you choose the guided call or the done-for-you option, I handle the technical complexity. You just need a computer and an internet connection.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I change my mind after booking?',
    answer: 'Yes. You can reschedule or cancel any booking through Cal.com. The Done-For-You tier also includes our satisfaction guarantee.',
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="section faq">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle">
      Everything you need to know before booking.
    </p>
    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map((faq) => (
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-question">{faq.question}</summary>
          <p class="faq-answer">{faq.answer}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-list {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .faq-question {
    padding: 24px 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .faq-question::after {
    content: '+';
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    transition: transform 0.2s;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-left: 16px;
  }

  .faq-item[open] .faq-question::after {
    content: '-';
  }

  .faq-answer {
    padding: 0 0 24px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
</style>
